cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.RO, cs.CE. 

The paper proposes a machine learning method to predict solution values for binary variables in Mixed Integer Programming (MIP) problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as they are also related to machine learning and optimization. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which makes cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. Finally, the paper presents computational evaluations, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
